///

///Instalacja
@NODE Instalacja "2.1 Installation"

	@{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

	To run the programme first you must unpack the archive to any
directory on your disk. Now the programme can be run (if @{"required components" LINK Wymagania}
are installed.

@{i}Notes:@{ui}

I.	If you'd been using previous versions of the programme you should
	delete ADR.x.prefs and ADR.x.cfg (where x are successive numbers
        starting from 1) from env:mui/ and envarch:mui/ directories.

II.	The programme is developed in Polish and that's its default language.
	There are a few additional languages available. If your language is
	not supported and you don't want (or can't) use Polish, you should
	properly configure locale settings in your system. Add English or
	German (or other) to "Preferred languages" to receive setting like
	this:

        xxxxx (your language)
	English/Deutsch (or any other available with the programme).

	Now the programme will run in a chosen language.

@ENDNODE
///
///Shell
@NODE Shell "2.2 Shell"

	@{b}@{u}Command line parameters@{uu}@{ub}

In case of starting the programme from command line (Shell/CLI) use:

AutoDocReader FILE_NAME/A
where:
	FILE_NAME is full name of a file with it's path.

The programme will load given file at start if only it exist in this location.
This way of running the programme is intended for using AutoDocReader as
an external viewer for other programmes. That's why the GUI is simplified when
compared with the one for Workbench/Ambient starting.

For example, in case of DOpus 4.1x: define autodoc filetype and add
"AutoDocReader {f}" action for double-click. Now you can view documents is
easy way.

FILE_NAME argument can also be the name of an ADR base file (#?.adr). The
programme will load and open that base then.

@ENDNODE
///
///Tooltypes
@NODE Tooltypes "2.3 Tooltypes"

	@{b}@{u}Workbench/Ambient parameters (tooltypes)@{uu}@{ub}

Running the programme from Workbencha/Ambienta gives you, beside "full" GUI,
a chance of changing the way AutoDocReader works. It is possible by means of
parameters in the programme's icon (tooltypes).

Available parameters have been divided into function groups.

@{u}1. Group View - GUI settings@{uu}

@{b}View.TinyGUI@{ub}
Tooltype defining what kind of GUI should the programme use.
By default, starting AutoDocReader from Workbench/Ambient results in "full"
GUI - it means access to autodoc database is available. Simply active this
tooltype if you want to run the programme in viewer mode (like in case
of running it from command line).

@{b}View.NoSelFunc@{ub}
This tooltype switches on/off auto-marking of first available function of
opened files.
By default, opened file is analyzed, its index is shown and a content of
a first position on the index is displayed.

@{b}View.ASL_Pattern@{ub}
Tooltype which can be used to define wildcards for ASL file requester used
while loading files.

@{b}View.TabSize@{ub}
This tooltype defines the way the "TAB" (0x09) code is displayed.
When AutoDocReader finds "TAB" code in text, it'll convert it into defined
number of spaces.
Accepted range of value: 1 - 16 spaces (default: 7)

@{b}View.FunSize@{ub}
With this tooltype you can define how many spaces will precede displayed name
of a section (e.g NAME, OPTIONS).
Accepted range of value: 1 -32 spaces (default: 0)

@{b}View.TxtSize@{ub}
This tooltype define number of spaces preceding each displayed line of text.
Accepted range of value: 1 -32 spaces (default: 3)

@{u}2. Group Base - base operations settings@{uu}

@{b}Base.AutoOpen@{ub}
This tooltype define if AutoDocReader should open recently used base (with
functions and sections selection) at start.

@{b}Base.Default@{ub}
Tooltype defining name and location of default base of autodoc files. You
can give here a name of a base to open at start if Base.AutoOpen tooltype is
active.

@ENDNODE
///

///MENU_Projekt
@NODE Menu_Projekt "3.1.1 Menu/Project"

	@{u}Menu/Project: File@{uu}

@{b}File/Open:@{ub}
	This options opens file requester in which you can choose a file to
	display not available in the base of autodoc files. This option is
	independent from selected tab Base/File.

@{b}File/Save:@{ub}
	This options opens file reqester allowing us to select directory and
	name for saving current document. Action depends on active tab -
	with "Base" tab active document from file base will be saved, with
	"File" tab active last opened document will be saved.
	Documents are saved in format not depending on group @{"View" LINK Tooltypes}
	settings.

@{b}File/Close:@{ub}
	Choosing this option will close a file and cleans display in document
	window. The option is available only when "File" tab is active.

	@{u}Menu/Project: Base@{uu}

@{b}Base/Open:@{ub}
	This options opens filerequester in which we can choose a file of
	previously prepared autodoc files base.

@{b}Base/Refresh:@{ub}
	This option auto-actualize the whole defined base. All files are
	rescanned to actualize changes in source documents.

@{b}Base/Save:@{ub}
	This options opens file reqester allowing us to select directory and
	name for saving current autodoc files base. Newly created, imported or
	modified base have to be saved to actualize an archive.

@{b}Base/Close:@{ub}
	This options is useful if you need to create a new base when one is
	already opened. Just close current one with "Base/Close".

	@{u}Menu/Project: About the programme@{uu}

@{b}About the programme:@{ub}
	Opens a small window where all people involved in this project are
	mentioned.

	@{u}Menu/Project: About MUI@{uu}

@{b}About MUI:@{ub}
	Opens a window with list of people involved in MUI libraries
	development.

	@{u}Menu/Project: Quit@{uu}

@{b}Quit:@{ub}
	This options closes opened documents and quits the programme.

@ENDNODE
///
///MENU_Edycja
@NODE Menu_Edycja "3.1.2 Menu/Edit"

	@{u}Menu/Edit: Base structure@{uu}

@{b}Edit/Base structure@{ub}

Opens a small window in which we can edit a base of autodoc files.
There are three options available:

@{b}Group@{ub}
	This one allows to add new group (gadget "Add") or to modify the name
	of an existing group (gadget "Change").
	Use a string gadget to enter a name of added or modified group.

@{b}File(s)@{ub}
	"Add" opens an ASL requester to select files to be added to the base.
	Files will be added in a marked place in a base. In case of no place
	is selected, files will be added in main group of a base.

@{b}Selected@{ub}
	"Deselect" removes a selection from structure window. It is needed
	when there is a new object to be placed on the highest level of the
	structure.
	"Delete" - deletes selected objects (or groups of objects) from the
	base.

If there is need to move an object-tree to a different place, simply use
"drag'n'drop" technique to do it and place it in desired part of a structure.

@ENDNODE
