///

///Okno - Baza
@NODE Okno_Baza "3.2.1 Main window/Base"

	@{u}Autodoc files base window@{uu}

On the left side of the main window a few windows for managing autodoc
files database are available when the programme is started from
Workbench/Ambient.

@{b}Gadget: File selection@{ub}
	Opens an ASL requester which allows to select a base of files to load.

@{b}Window: name of currently opened base@{ub}
	This window contains the name of opened file base. When new base is
	created, it'll be named during saving it.

@{b}Window: Base containing a list of available documents@{ub}
	The window shows a current structure of autodoc files base. You can
	use drag'n'drop to move its elements. Other edit features are available
	in @{"Menu/Edit/Base structure" LINK MENU_Edycja}.

@{b}Window: Fast search pattern@{ub}
	This window allows fast searching for file or function.
	The search is performend after entering a patter in a string gadget and
	pressing "enter" on the keyboard. The search is not case sensitive. When
	an object is found, it is displayed. If it's not the one we search, we
	can click search gadget again to continue. We will be informed if there
	are no more matching objects.

@ENDNODE

///
///Okno - Spis
@NODE Okno_Spis "3.2.2 Main window/Table of contents"

	@{u}Selected document table of contents window@{uu}

@{b}Window: Library of document base@{ub}
	This field contains a name of library of document base.

@{b}Window: List of available document elements@{ub}
	This window contains a list functions/parameters available in
	a document. The choice of function to display is made by clicking on
	function/parameter name.

@ENDNODE
///
///Okno - Dokument
@NODE Okno_Dokument "3.2.3 Main window/Document"

	@{u}Selected document contents window@{uu}

@{b}Gadget: File selection@{ub}
	Opens an ASL requester which allows to select a base of files to load.

@{b}Window: Name of selected document@{ub}
	This field contains the name of selected or loaded document.

@{b}Gadget: Previous file@{ub}
	Displays previously viewed document.

@{b}Gadget: Next file@{ub}
	Displays next viewed document.

@{b}Object: Example@{ub}
	Object informes if there is any text in an example window. Thanks to
	this, there's no need to check "Example" sheet every time.

@{b}Window: Arguments and parameteres of functions@{ub}
	Arguments and parameters of functions (NAME and SYNOPSIS sections in
	autodoc file) ar displayed here.

@{b}Window: Document contents@{ub}
	It is used to display contents of particular fields of
	function/parameter. The programme makes browsing it easier by
	autoformating a document (the same gaps between fields, spaces
	preceding lines etc.)

@{b}Window: Example@{ub}
	This window display EXAMPLE section of selected function/parameter.

Contents of the window (or its part) can be copied to system clipboard
as well.
@{i}
Not all of authors of autodoc files follow the rules of creating them, hence
it is possible that a file is displayed incorrectly. Corrections in sorce file
are needed to get proper presentation in such case. The programme has been
tested with a large number of documents and a lot of possible unobservances of
rules are implemented. However, it cannot be guaranteed that all unproperly
prepared files will be properly read and displayed.
@{ui}
@{b}Properly created autodoc file is analyzed and displayed by AutoDocReader
without any problems.@{ub}

@ENDNODE
///

///Okno - Szukaj
@NODE Okno_Szukaj "3.2.4 Main window/Searching"

	@{uSearching in file contents@{uu}

The programme allows to search for a requested string in a text. Search can be
performed for currently opened file or for all the files in ADR base.

@{b}Gadget: search mode@{ub}
	Selection of search mode. It can be performed for:
	"Document" - searches only in opened document;
	"Base of files" - searches in all the files in base.

@{b}Window: Search pattern@{ub}
	Enter the text to be searched into the string gadget. Search is
	performed after pressing "enter" on the keyboard.

@{b}Gadget: Select previous@{ub}
	This gadget allows to go back to a previously found text.

@{b}Gadget: Select next@{ub}
	This gadget allows to go forward to a later found text or to find next
	one matching the pattern, if the current is the last one found.

@ENDNODE
